### ============================================================
### Enterprise SaaS — Billing & Subscription Example
### ============================================================
### Variables (adjust to match your local JWT tokens)
### Admin token:   role=admin, org_id=11111111-...
### Finance token: role=finance, org_id=11111111-...
### Member token:  role=member, org_id=11111111-...
### ============================================================

@base = http://localhost:3000/v1
@admin_token = Bearer <admin-jwt-token>
@finance_token = Bearer <finance-jwt-token>
@member_token = Bearer <member-jwt-token>

### ============================================================
### 1. CUSTOMERS
### ============================================================

### Create a new customer (admin)
POST {{base}}/customers
Authorization: {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "NewCo Industries",
  "email": "billing@newco.com",
  "plan": "starter",
  "credit_limit_cents": 50000
}

### List customers — filter by plan
GET {{base}}/customers?filter[plan]=starter
Authorization: {{admin_token}}

### List customers — search by name
GET {{base}}/customers?search=Acme
Authorization: {{admin_token}}

### Try to create customer with credit limit exceeding plan
### (should fail: free plan max is 0)
POST {{base}}/customers
Authorization: {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Cheapskate Ltd",
  "email": "info@cheapskate.com",
  "plan": "free",
  "credit_limit_cents": 10000
}

### Try to skip plan tiers (free -> pro, should fail)
PATCH {{base}}/customers/bbbbbbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbbbbbbbbbb
Authorization: {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "plan": "pro"
}

### Valid plan upgrade (starter -> pro)
PATCH {{base}}/customers/bbbbbbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbb-bbbbbbbbbbbb
Authorization: {{admin_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "plan": "pro"
}

### ============================================================
### 2. INVOICES
### ============================================================

### Create a draft invoice (auto-generates invoice_number)
POST {{base}}/invoices
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "aaaaaaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaa-aaaaaaaaaaaa",
  "subtotal_cents": 100000,
  "tax_cents": 8000,
  "total_cents": 108000,
  "due_date": "2026-04-15"
}

### Try to send invoice as member (should fail: insufficient role)
### Replace <invoice-id> with the ID returned from create above
PATCH {{base}}/invoices/<invoice-id>
Authorization: {{member_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "sent"
}

### Move invoice from draft to pending (finance)
PATCH {{base}}/invoices/<invoice-id>
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "pending"
}

### Send invoice (pending -> sent, finance role)
PATCH {{base}}/invoices/<invoice-id>
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "sent"
}

### Try invalid transition: sent -> draft (should fail)
PATCH {{base}}/invoices/<invoice-id>
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "draft"
}

### Try to void as non-admin (should fail)
PATCH {{base}}/invoices/<invoice-id>
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "void"
}

### Try to create invoice for suspended customer (should fail)
POST {{base}}/invoices
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_id": "cccccccc-cccc-cccc-cccc-cccccccccccc",
  "subtotal_cents": 5000,
  "tax_cents": 400,
  "total_cents": 5400,
  "due_date": "2026-05-01"
}

### List invoices — filter by status
GET {{base}}/invoices?filter[status]=sent
Authorization: {{finance_token}}

### ============================================================
### 3. PAYMENTS
### ============================================================

### Record a payment against the sent invoice
POST {{base}}/payments
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoice_id": "<invoice-id>",
  "amount_cents": 50000,
  "method": "card",
  "reference_number": "ch_abc123"
}

### Try to overpay (should fail: exceeds remaining balance)
POST {{base}}/payments
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoice_id": "<invoice-id>",
  "amount_cents": 999999,
  "method": "card"
}

### Record remaining payment to fully cover the invoice
POST {{base}}/payments
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoice_id": "<invoice-id>",
  "amount_cents": 58000,
  "method": "bank_transfer",
  "reference_number": "bt_xyz789"
}

### Mark first payment as completed
### (if this is the last payment, invoice auto-updates to "paid")
PATCH {{base}}/payments/<payment-id-1>
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "completed"
}

### Mark second payment as completed -> invoice should auto-mark as paid
PATCH {{base}}/payments/<payment-id-2>
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "completed"
}

### Verify invoice is now "paid"
GET {{base}}/invoices/<invoice-id>
Authorization: {{finance_token}}

### Try to modify a completed payment (should fail)
PATCH {{base}}/payments/<payment-id-1>
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "refunded"
}

### Try to record payment against a paid invoice (should fail)
POST {{base}}/payments
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "invoice_id": "<invoice-id>",
  "amount_cents": 1000,
  "method": "card"
}

### ============================================================
### 4. AUDIT TRAIL
### ============================================================

### View audit logs (direct SQL query or custom endpoint)
### Audit entries are written automatically by controllers:
### - Plan changes on customers
### - All invoice status transitions
### - Auto-paid invoice events triggered by payment completion

### List payments — filter by method
GET {{base}}/payments?filter[method]=card
Authorization: {{finance_token}}

### List payments — filter by status
GET {{base}}/payments?filter[status]=completed
Authorization: {{finance_token}}
